WEBVTT

00:05.570 --> 00:08.921
There hasn't been a murder here
in a long time.

00:08.965 --> 00:10.358
Now there are two.

00:10.401 --> 00:12.403
Woman: One of you
will be chosen as an envoy

00:12.447 --> 00:14.536
and help usher in
the Bridge.

00:14.579 --> 00:17.104
I'm not the Earth agent
sent to disrupt The Bridge,

00:17.147 --> 00:19.671
but someone is
turning Mooners against it.

00:19.715 --> 00:23.849
IO warned us.
It predicted all of this.

00:23.893 --> 00:27.070
Why would Mooners not want
to keep this all for themselves?

00:27.114 --> 00:29.638
Because this isn't Earth.

00:29.681 --> 00:32.423
Everything we do
is for The Bridge.

00:32.467 --> 00:34.469
What's all this?Trouble comes.

00:37.733 --> 00:40.692
- [grunting]

00:40.736 --> 00:43.869
[tense music]

00:43.913 --> 00:46.220
♪

00:46.263 --> 00:48.744
- Stay back!

00:48.787 --> 00:51.660
- [grunting]

00:51.703 --> 00:58.580
♪

01:10.157 --> 01:12.855
- ♪ I went behind enemy lines
to fetch a pail of water ♪

01:12.898 --> 01:14.900
- Ahh!

01:14.944 --> 01:16.206
- ♪ A farmer saw,
but he did not draw ♪

01:16.250 --> 01:18.078
♪ Because I was under--

01:18.121 --> 01:24.954
♪

01:26.042 --> 01:27.957
- He's nay breathing!

01:28.000 --> 01:30.568
- Then leave him.
Indira's out there alone!

01:30.612 --> 01:34.572
♪

01:34.616 --> 01:38.098
Indira, Indira!

01:38.141 --> 01:43.538
♪

01:43.581 --> 01:47.411
- [whimpering]
Ahh!

01:47.455 --> 01:49.413
- I've got you.

01:49.457 --> 01:56.246
♪

01:57.639 --> 01:59.597
- Thank you.

01:59.641 --> 02:02.687
♪

02:02.731 --> 02:05.037
- Paul, Arlo!

02:05.081 --> 02:07.257
- We're here.

02:07.301 --> 02:10.173
♪

02:10.217 --> 02:11.653
- Who goes?

02:11.696 --> 02:13.611
- Fire crew.

02:13.655 --> 02:20.575
♪

02:27.495 --> 02:30.454
[whistles]

02:30.498 --> 02:33.631
♪

02:33.675 --> 02:35.633
[whistles]

02:35.677 --> 02:42.597
♪

02:55.044 --> 02:57.002
[whistles]

03:03.400 --> 03:05.489
- Tomm's gone.

03:05.533 --> 03:09.537
- This wasn't an attack.
It was an extraction.

03:09.580 --> 03:12.670
- We thought he was dead.
- The sedative.

03:12.714 --> 03:14.281
They got him out.

03:14.324 --> 03:16.065
Whatever they've been planning,

03:16.108 --> 03:18.198
they need him
to see it through.

03:18.241 --> 03:21.070
This could be what
Chill's warning was about.

03:21.113 --> 03:22.724
- The First Wavers are being
celebrated tomorrow.

03:22.767 --> 03:23.986
- Your son.

03:24.029 --> 03:25.727
- All
of Moonhaven will be there.

03:25.770 --> 03:28.556
- If this were Earth,
I'd expect an attack or a bomb.

03:28.599 --> 03:30.558
- No, IO would prevent that.

03:30.601 --> 03:32.864
It won't be a bomb
that will destroy us.

03:32.908 --> 03:35.040
It will be doubt.

03:36.216 --> 03:39.175
[dramatic music]

03:39.219 --> 03:46.095
♪

04:23.480 --> 04:26.396
- Where you now stand,
there was nothing.

04:26.440 --> 04:29.965
Our land was dry-barren
and scrape

04:30.008 --> 04:32.837
without life or meaning.

04:32.881 --> 04:38.365
As First Wavers, you will soon
bring both back to the Mother.

04:38.408 --> 04:42.891
We have spent our lives
studying the world

04:42.934 --> 04:45.110
we have been tasked to remake.

04:45.154 --> 04:48.505
As we know the mountains
and valleys of the Mother,

04:48.549 --> 04:52.379
so we have sought
to understand the people.

04:52.422 --> 04:56.731
Make no mistake.
You sail into a storm.

04:56.774 --> 04:59.168
When you leave
on the transport ships,

04:59.211 --> 05:03.259
you will be two days
from footfall on Earth.

05:03.303 --> 05:07.263
Nay forget your mission.

05:07.307 --> 05:10.179
The tools you bring
the Mother from IO

05:10.222 --> 05:12.355
are not only
to fix what is broken.

05:12.399 --> 05:15.358
You serve those
yet to be born.

05:15.402 --> 05:17.752
You will
create new beginnings,

05:17.795 --> 05:20.711
the Bridge Zones,
where our mistakes,

05:20.755 --> 05:24.454
humanity's mistakes,
will be forever cherished,

05:24.498 --> 05:28.502
understood,
and never repeated.

05:28.545 --> 05:31.374
The future is better.

05:31.418 --> 05:33.724
all: The future is better.

05:33.768 --> 05:36.553
- You will now receive
your Bridge Zone assignments.

05:36.597 --> 05:38.338
Three landing sites,

05:38.381 --> 05:40.557
kept secret
for your protection,

05:40.601 --> 05:44.300
have been selected within each
of the 12 Bridge Zones.

05:44.344 --> 05:46.084
- Circle Six,

05:46.128 --> 05:50.915
your Earth landing zone
will be Sahara Desert, North.

05:50.959 --> 05:53.135
- It's a trap!

05:53.178 --> 05:56.356
The Earthers will
kill us all when we land.

05:56.399 --> 06:00.098
Free Lune!
They'll never let us live!

06:00.142 --> 06:03.450
It's a trap!
Stop the Bridge!

06:03.493 --> 06:05.452
The Earthers
are gonna kill us all!

06:05.495 --> 06:08.498
Are you listening to me?
You're all gonna die!

06:08.542 --> 06:10.805
Listen to me!

06:10.848 --> 06:15.331
[dramatic music]

06:22.904 --> 06:25.341
- Come in.

06:25.385 --> 06:28.562
Tomm must have been
working this a long time.

06:28.605 --> 06:31.739
A separatist Moon,
in full control of IO

06:31.782 --> 06:33.349
and all it can do.

06:33.393 --> 06:36.657
- You gotta appreciate
the big swing.

06:36.700 --> 06:39.790
- He was Ultra Ops in the war.

06:39.834 --> 06:42.532
He worked alone, but he told me
his nickname was The Battalion.

06:42.576 --> 06:44.578
- If he was Ultra,

06:44.621 --> 06:47.537
then anything he ever said
to you was for a reason.

06:47.581 --> 06:50.975
The training's all
about the long game.

06:51.019 --> 06:53.543
- I'm glad you're here, Bella.

06:53.587 --> 06:55.110
I'm alone now.

06:56.851 --> 06:59.244
The Council chair is refusing

06:59.288 --> 07:01.899
to let
the transport ships land.

07:01.943 --> 07:04.772
No one knows yet.
- Why would she do that?

07:04.815 --> 07:06.817
- I assume
she's looking for leverage.

07:06.861 --> 07:09.037
She wants to stay in power.

07:09.080 --> 07:12.519
Those ships are due to leave
for Earth in four days.

07:12.562 --> 07:14.042
- I've met Maite.

07:14.085 --> 07:16.740
She's had me watched
since my trial.

07:16.784 --> 07:18.873
- I need
to get those ships down

07:18.916 --> 07:21.441
before anyone else
finds out what she's done.

07:25.357 --> 07:26.794
Tomm's gun.

07:28.883 --> 07:30.450
Shoot me.

07:31.755 --> 07:37.239
Humankind is fallible,
but IO is not.

07:37.282 --> 07:40.111
I believe this
with everything I am.

07:40.155 --> 07:44.507
You have to believe
in something, Bella Sway.

07:44.551 --> 07:46.335
- Envoy, what are you doing?

07:46.378 --> 07:48.598
No!

07:48.642 --> 07:51.601
[eerie humming]

07:57.433 --> 08:00.305
[soft vocalization]

08:00.349 --> 08:03.265
♪

08:03.308 --> 08:07.008
- This is what
we are fighting for,

08:07.051 --> 08:10.315
to save us from ourselves.

08:10.359 --> 08:12.709
♪

08:12.753 --> 08:16.321
- I can get close to Maite.

08:16.365 --> 08:18.498
Let me help you.

08:18.541 --> 08:24.199
♪

08:25.374 --> 08:28.769
- So landing in the Sahara.

08:28.812 --> 08:30.901
- In the middle of the desert?

08:30.945 --> 08:33.034
- Bedouin nomads
used to live there

08:33.077 --> 08:35.776
before the hyper-simooms.

08:35.819 --> 08:38.822
- Um, most touchdowns are far
from population.

08:38.866 --> 08:41.303
They're kept secret so that
we can protect the IO tech

08:41.346 --> 08:42.870
until it can protect us.

08:42.913 --> 08:46.569
- Good, the less contact
with Earthers, the better.

08:46.613 --> 08:49.877
- There are some Waver circles
going into cities to teach.

08:49.920 --> 08:51.792
- Well, you're lucky then.

08:51.835 --> 08:53.620
- Uh, why is he lucky?

08:53.663 --> 08:55.273
I would like him
to teach the people.

08:55.317 --> 08:56.753
Maybe they could teach him.

08:56.797 --> 08:58.276
- And what would
they teach a Mooner

08:58.320 --> 08:59.930
but how to ruin what works?

08:59.974 --> 09:01.976
Your talk is easy, Paul.

09:02.019 --> 09:04.456
Lone knows our son
launches into darkness.

09:04.500 --> 09:07.242
Wish'll find out the truths
about Earthers soon enough.

09:07.285 --> 09:09.287
- The truth?

09:09.331 --> 09:11.899
- We know them better
than they know themselves.

09:11.942 --> 09:15.772
We fix everyall for them,
and they would war us all

09:15.816 --> 09:17.426
if we dropped our guard.

09:17.469 --> 09:19.820
- But they are us,
and we are them.

09:21.299 --> 09:23.867
- The time
for child-speak is past.

09:23.911 --> 09:27.915
- Wish, you have nothing
to learn from the Mother?

09:27.958 --> 09:32.484
- I mean,
I would listen if they spoke,

09:32.528 --> 09:36.010
but the hungry
only talk of food.

09:36.053 --> 09:38.316
- You're smiles, Fritz?

09:38.360 --> 09:40.057
The boy now
babbles your jabber.

09:40.101 --> 09:41.755
- Maybe Fritz taught me
how to think for myself.

09:41.798 --> 09:44.366
- Well, then think, think.

09:44.409 --> 09:46.716
This arrogant swagger
is not the boy I raised.

09:46.760 --> 09:49.719
- No, he's not, Paul.
He's a man now.

09:51.242 --> 09:55.029
- Mooners know strength
is weakness.

09:55.072 --> 09:58.467
Do you hear yourself?
And you?

09:58.510 --> 10:01.557
Where are you in all this?
Your silence is loud.

10:01.601 --> 10:04.342
- He needs
to know how to survive.

10:04.386 --> 10:06.693
A good heart is enough here,
not up there.

10:06.736 --> 10:09.391
- A good heart
is enough anywhere.

10:09.434 --> 10:11.393
If it's not, then what are we
trying to save on Earth?

10:11.436 --> 10:14.352
The greed, the anger?

10:14.396 --> 10:18.966
Wish, your life should be proof
that we should survive.

10:19.009 --> 10:21.838
- And the Earthers
who live by no rules?

10:21.882 --> 10:24.275
What of the attack
this morning?

10:24.319 --> 10:26.321
- What attack?

10:26.364 --> 10:28.671
- You have not told Lone?

10:28.715 --> 10:32.196
A fire where the Envoy's guard
was recovering,

10:32.240 --> 10:34.068
and IO sees nothing?

10:34.111 --> 10:36.679
There are Earthers
amongst us causing chaos,

10:36.723 --> 10:38.463
and your pilot is involved.

10:38.507 --> 10:40.204
- Bella helps us,

10:40.248 --> 10:42.903
and it's Mooners who have
turned against the Bridge.

10:42.946 --> 10:46.254
They've shed their marks,
and it spreads like poison.

10:47.777 --> 10:49.344
- What do you mean,
shed their marks?

10:51.912 --> 10:53.783
- Wish.

10:55.132 --> 10:56.917
Wish!

10:57.874 --> 11:00.007
Wish, wait.

11:00.050 --> 11:02.966
This is the panic and crumble
that comes with change.

11:03.010 --> 11:05.708
Truelune stays the course.

11:05.752 --> 11:08.363
- Truelune?

11:08.406 --> 11:10.931
How long would you keep me from
seeing things the way they are?

11:10.974 --> 11:12.802
I'm going to fight a war,

11:12.846 --> 11:14.369
and you want me
to stay a child.

11:14.412 --> 11:16.153
- Fritz has you thinking--

11:16.197 --> 11:19.679
- Fritz didn't make me
think anything, okay?

11:19.722 --> 11:22.333
Fritz isn't like you.
- No, he's not.

11:23.552 --> 11:25.467
- He isn't a fool.

11:35.912 --> 11:38.698
- Paul Sarno?
- Yeah.

11:52.146 --> 11:55.366
[soft music]

11:55.410 --> 12:02.243
♪

12:12.644 --> 12:14.559
- Go.

12:18.955 --> 12:21.044
I'm happy you came.

12:21.088 --> 12:23.046
- Saves you the trouble
of having me followed.

12:25.527 --> 12:28.356
Why won't you
let the ships land?

12:28.399 --> 12:30.401
You know the damage
you're causing.

12:30.445 --> 12:34.841
- Ah, the Envoy speaks
through you with Earth words,

12:34.884 --> 12:36.930
but what does your heart say?

12:39.149 --> 12:42.326
We are taught
to nay believe in destiny.

12:43.545 --> 12:46.591
From your eyes,
one step leads to another.

12:48.985 --> 12:50.900
But from these eyes,

12:50.944 --> 12:53.511
you were called
and came as planned.

12:53.555 --> 12:56.819
- Maite, you've given people
on Earth hope.

12:56.863 --> 12:59.779
Can you see the risk in that?

12:59.822 --> 13:02.042
You've let them imagine
there's another way.

13:02.085 --> 13:04.305
You take that back now,

13:04.348 --> 13:06.133
and their hope
will die for good.

13:06.176 --> 13:08.265
- Do you have hope, Bella?

13:08.309 --> 13:12.704
- It's not about me.
None of this is about me.

13:12.748 --> 13:15.403
Those ships mean
things could change.

13:15.446 --> 13:18.580
Let them land.
- I want to know it's safe.

13:18.623 --> 13:20.582
There are those on the Mother

13:20.625 --> 13:23.280
that profit
from her destruction.

13:23.324 --> 13:25.935
Do they wait in darkness
to destroy us?

13:27.371 --> 13:30.897
I want to know
what trouble IO saw ahead.

13:32.246 --> 13:34.248
- It saw you.

13:35.727 --> 13:38.165
You are the trouble.

13:51.134 --> 13:53.180
- The pilot has moved you.

13:53.223 --> 13:56.748
- You want me to share
what I cannot understand.

13:56.792 --> 13:59.055
- She speaks
only for the Mother.

13:59.099 --> 14:01.710
It's hard to hear.
- No.

14:01.753 --> 14:04.104
It's nay what she says.

14:04.147 --> 14:06.889
It's who she is.
It's how she's come.

14:06.933 --> 14:10.110
She's the message
I've been waiting for.

14:10.153 --> 14:12.808
- Her blood sister, the Mooner,

14:12.852 --> 14:14.244
I've learned
she worked with those

14:14.288 --> 14:16.203
who wish to stop the Bridge.

14:16.246 --> 14:17.857
These rebels divide us,

14:17.900 --> 14:20.076
and your delaying the ships
only aids their cause.

14:20.120 --> 14:23.166
- Their cause is just.
They doubt.

14:23.210 --> 14:26.866
They're hot-riled by fear,
but I am not afraid.

14:28.258 --> 14:30.391
[laughs]

14:30.434 --> 14:33.437
Something bigger-better
comes to save us all,

14:33.481 --> 14:35.962
something even our Dreamers
could not dream.

14:38.660 --> 14:40.575
You think me mad?

14:43.099 --> 14:45.885
- No.

14:45.928 --> 14:50.193
I believe in you.
Trust yourself, Maite.

14:50.237 --> 14:54.545
Trust that you are doing
the right thing for all of us.

14:54.589 --> 14:57.766
We will follow you
wherever you lead.

14:59.333 --> 15:01.901
- Gratz for your counsel.

15:04.381 --> 15:07.036
Sonda.

15:07.080 --> 15:14.000
♪

15:37.371 --> 15:38.938
- Where's Paul?

15:38.981 --> 15:42.245
- It's his Palmi.
- His what?

15:42.289 --> 15:45.292
- His blood mother goes to air.
He's gone to see her.

15:45.335 --> 15:47.250
- I thought you don't meet
your blood parents.

15:47.294 --> 15:50.123
- At our birth and their death,
we meet.

15:50.166 --> 15:52.038
The Palmi is the farewell.

15:53.213 --> 15:55.606
You should go to him.

15:55.650 --> 15:57.782
- If it were me,
I'd want to be alone.

15:57.826 --> 15:59.132
- He wouldn't.

16:01.830 --> 16:03.919
What happened this morning?

16:03.963 --> 16:06.574
No one will say more.

16:06.617 --> 16:08.750
- Mooners have turned
against the Bridge.

16:08.793 --> 16:11.013
The Envoy's guard is involved.

16:11.057 --> 16:13.015
- An Earther.

16:13.059 --> 16:16.366
- I can't tell you who or what
he's fighting for,

16:16.410 --> 16:19.543
but you know, don't you?

16:19.587 --> 16:22.677
You hear "Earther,"
and you know the whole story.

16:22.720 --> 16:25.332
Like when you look at me.

16:25.375 --> 16:27.334
- Or you me.

16:27.377 --> 16:30.119
You think this is easy
to live this way.

16:30.163 --> 16:32.556
You think I'm cruel and blind
to my lover's pain?

16:32.600 --> 16:34.341
- Which one?

16:35.995 --> 16:38.606
- What is strange to you
is not to me.

16:38.649 --> 16:42.871
- Yeah, well, a hundred years
of all this bullshit,

16:42.914 --> 16:45.047
of you making yourselves
better than us,

16:45.091 --> 16:47.832
and it took a trained operative
about ten minutes

16:47.876 --> 16:49.617
to turn you all
against yourselves.

16:49.660 --> 16:53.447
- We're not broken so easy.
It won't work.

16:53.490 --> 16:56.493
- I think it's working, sister.

16:56.537 --> 16:59.018
- I should rip out my mark
and beg them

16:59.061 --> 17:02.369
to stop the Bridge,
but I want my child to go.

17:02.412 --> 17:05.937
I want him to make things
better for Earth.

17:05.981 --> 17:08.288
What more do you need from me?

17:10.116 --> 17:17.036
♪

18:04.431 --> 18:06.389
- How now?

18:09.392 --> 18:12.265
- I still beat.

18:14.005 --> 18:16.356
Still here.

18:21.230 --> 18:22.971
- Mada.

18:24.668 --> 18:26.540
- Boy.

18:37.899 --> 18:39.901
- Here.

18:47.343 --> 18:50.129
- Good life, ya?

18:50.172 --> 18:52.131
- Yeah.

18:53.262 --> 18:54.655
- Talk.

18:56.265 --> 18:58.485
This time is what we have.

19:03.054 --> 19:05.100
- I am lost.

19:06.232 --> 19:09.713
Trying to hold it together.

19:09.757 --> 19:11.628
I'm too weak.

19:13.239 --> 19:15.980
- I see no weakness.

19:17.417 --> 19:21.160
I see strength
in a man who is sad.

19:26.774 --> 19:30.169
- My son goes to Earth.

19:31.431 --> 19:34.564
We've talked about it
since he was a wisp,

19:34.608 --> 19:37.176
since he came to us
seven years ago.

19:39.134 --> 19:42.181
Curious boy with a wide smile.

19:42.224 --> 19:45.096
♪

19:45.140 --> 19:49.449
He swaggers now,
pushes me away.

19:51.146 --> 19:55.542
I see the man he will become,

19:55.585 --> 19:59.589
but the boy inside,

19:59.633 --> 20:01.635
I told that boy,

20:01.678 --> 20:05.987
trust Truelune,
trust our purpose.

20:06.030 --> 20:08.990
♪

20:09.033 --> 20:13.342
I taught him to leave,
and now I doubt.

20:14.648 --> 20:18.217
- All children leave.

20:18.260 --> 20:20.741
Time sees to that.

20:22.830 --> 20:27.313
This is not the first time
Truelune has been tested.

20:28.923 --> 20:33.319
Sometimes, we feel lost.
Our foot is in the air.

20:33.362 --> 20:36.496
Where will it go?

20:36.539 --> 20:41.414
But it always comes back,

20:41.457 --> 20:43.894
down to the ground.

20:45.331 --> 20:49.422
The way forward,
across the bridge.

20:51.685 --> 20:54.731
We do not walk alone.

20:54.775 --> 20:59.301
♪

20:59.345 --> 21:01.521
Boy called?

21:03.087 --> 21:05.264
- Wish.

21:07.918 --> 21:09.920
- Boy.

21:09.964 --> 21:13.924
♪

21:13.968 --> 21:18.581
- Paul.
My name is Paul, Mada.

21:18.625 --> 21:20.583
- Paul.

21:22.759 --> 21:26.110
I was called Gnoc.

21:26.154 --> 21:32.682
♪

21:32.726 --> 21:34.641
Up do.

21:36.773 --> 21:39.385
This ends for me.

21:39.428 --> 21:46.305
♪

22:13.941 --> 22:17.292
both: I will honor the blood.

22:17.336 --> 22:21.427
But it will not bind me.

22:21.470 --> 22:25.387
I will be family to all.

22:25.431 --> 22:29.043
Put the past behind me.

22:31.001 --> 22:34.440
- I will sing to the Moon

22:34.483 --> 22:38.661
and let her console me.

22:38.705 --> 22:45.668
♪

23:38.199 --> 23:41.289
- Why do you meet
your blood parents at all?

23:41.332 --> 23:43.291
- Uh, it's a tribute

23:43.334 --> 23:48.339
to the old ways when blood
was more important than water.

23:48.383 --> 23:50.690
You've heard of the rebellion?

23:50.733 --> 23:54.520
- A hundred years ago,
before the blackout.

23:54.563 --> 23:57.479
- 143.

23:57.523 --> 24:02.658
The first settlers were quick
to divide on family lines.

24:02.702 --> 24:07.620
One tribe tried to control IO.
Earth shut it down.

24:07.663 --> 24:09.535
Was a bloody mess.

24:09.578 --> 24:12.451
- Mm.
- IO watched.

24:12.494 --> 24:16.150
It was decided
that they should start again.

24:16.193 --> 24:18.544
New settlers arrived,
and yeah, the blackout,

24:18.587 --> 24:22.417
and water families
took the place of blood.

24:22.461 --> 24:25.507
- Because a family
leads to a tribe,

24:25.551 --> 24:28.597
leads to a nation,
leads to a war.

24:28.641 --> 24:32.166
- Hm,
blood leads to blood, we say.

24:39.129 --> 24:40.957
- Leave us please.

24:42.698 --> 24:45.353
Sonda.

24:45.396 --> 24:47.573
I hope you've come
to tell me the Council chair

24:47.616 --> 24:49.226
has changed her mind.

24:49.270 --> 24:50.793
By not letting the ships down,

24:50.837 --> 24:52.926
she is playing
right into the rebels' hands.

24:52.969 --> 24:55.755
- Envoy.

24:55.798 --> 24:58.409
I begged her
to let them land,

24:58.453 --> 25:00.324
to change her mind.

25:00.368 --> 25:02.849
I told her it's her duty
to call Council

25:02.892 --> 25:05.808
and speak for the light,
to see what Mooners feel--

25:05.852 --> 25:08.289
- If she doesn't stand up
and lead her people,

25:08.332 --> 25:10.987
these insurgent lies
will spread unchecked.

25:11.031 --> 25:12.641
She is beloved.

25:12.685 --> 25:16.297
She has your hearts,
but she leads you over a cliff.

25:16.340 --> 25:19.866
You are her second, yes?

25:19.909 --> 25:23.086
If Maite won't speak out,

25:23.130 --> 25:26.568
then maybe someone else
needs to stand up.

25:26.612 --> 25:28.962
We're running out of time.

25:29.005 --> 25:31.834
[tense music]

25:31.878 --> 25:38.841
♪

26:00.776 --> 26:03.866
- You're okay.

26:03.910 --> 26:07.653
♪

26:14.616 --> 26:17.488
- How, now, Bella.
Where's Paul?

26:17.532 --> 26:19.926
- He's celebrating Wish today.

26:19.969 --> 26:21.580
- The Three Circles.

26:21.623 --> 26:24.017
All of Wish's water parents
will come together later.

26:24.060 --> 26:27.150
- Yeah, more crazy shit.

26:27.194 --> 26:30.937
Can I, uh, show you something?

26:30.980 --> 26:33.635
I found this when Paul
and I went back

26:33.679 --> 26:34.984
to where Chill was killed.

26:35.028 --> 26:37.073
It was right where she fell.

26:37.117 --> 26:39.336
- A flower petal?

26:39.380 --> 26:42.557
- It's not real.
It's synthetic.

26:42.601 --> 26:46.735
I'd forgotten about it.
What's that?

26:46.779 --> 26:48.998
- This is called a magnifying--
- I know what it is.

26:49.042 --> 26:51.000
Why do you have one?

26:51.044 --> 26:53.829
- I had a Maker make it.
I like it.

26:53.873 --> 26:55.309
Crazy shit.

26:55.352 --> 26:58.704
- Okay.
- Hm?

26:58.747 --> 27:00.793
Hmm.

27:02.795 --> 27:06.799
This has been ripped
at the base.

27:06.842 --> 27:11.194
- Wow, so where's the rest
of the flower?

27:12.587 --> 27:15.982
- What did Strego say to Tomm
before he got shot?

27:16.025 --> 27:18.593
- He said,
"Where one world ends,

27:18.637 --> 27:20.856
the next one begins."

27:20.900 --> 27:22.641
- That's it?

27:22.684 --> 27:24.643
- Uh, when I called him,
he was upset.

27:24.686 --> 27:27.036
He said he'd done
something terrible.

27:27.080 --> 27:29.299
That's when I figured it out.

27:29.343 --> 27:31.737
I told him Chill was my sister.

27:31.780 --> 27:35.088
We heard Tomm,
and I told him to stay hidden.

27:35.131 --> 27:37.438
- Hmm.

27:37.481 --> 27:38.874
- There is something
I need to do.

27:38.918 --> 27:40.789
Can you--
- Detect?

27:40.833 --> 27:42.356
- Yeah.

27:55.064 --> 27:58.067
- Maite's craze has
created opportunity.

27:58.111 --> 28:01.810
She's lost her faith
in the Bridge,

28:01.854 --> 28:05.640
and even the Envoy
sees the need to remove her,

28:05.684 --> 28:07.381
as you predicted.

28:08.948 --> 28:10.863
Tomm?

28:13.213 --> 28:15.737
When Sirl sent word you were
waking up from the Singer,

28:15.781 --> 28:17.608
I didn't believe it.

28:17.652 --> 28:19.698
No one's ever taken that much.

28:19.741 --> 28:21.395
- No shit.

28:23.266 --> 28:25.355
- What was it like?

28:27.793 --> 28:32.014
- I saw
m-monsters in this world,

28:32.058 --> 28:34.495
and then they saw me in theirs.

28:36.584 --> 28:39.456
Every hesitation,

28:39.500 --> 28:43.243
every bad choice I ever made
happened all over again.

28:46.246 --> 28:48.074
- Give it time.

28:48.117 --> 28:49.597
You're back now.
I'm here.

28:49.640 --> 28:52.339
- No, I'm not being clear.
It was a gift.

28:53.514 --> 28:56.212
I saw where I am, Sonda,

28:56.256 --> 28:58.867
where I've been,
where I'm going.

28:59.781 --> 29:02.871
I saw us,
crowns, and thrones.

29:02.915 --> 29:05.874
I saw our future
on the new Moon.

29:05.918 --> 29:08.877
[dramatic music]

29:08.921 --> 29:15.754
♪

29:45.087 --> 29:49.004
- Meega.
Oh, oh, apologies, apologies.

29:49.048 --> 29:51.224
- Oh, I didn't think
I'd see you.

29:51.267 --> 29:55.097
- Well, the soothe of work.
- Mm-hmm.

29:55.141 --> 29:56.925
- Look at this.

29:56.969 --> 30:04.150
♪

30:04.193 --> 30:06.848
- A flower.
- Unreal, made by a Mooner.

30:06.892 --> 30:08.807
But yes, a flower.

30:08.850 --> 30:11.853
- Why would he kill her
for a flower?

30:11.897 --> 30:15.117
- There's only a little to see
before the fight, but watch.

30:15.161 --> 30:19.905
♪

30:19.948 --> 30:21.558
- It's telling her where to go.

30:21.602 --> 30:23.430
- Like a compass rose.

30:23.473 --> 30:26.041
- I've never seen anything
like that before.

30:26.085 --> 30:27.826
Where does it lead?

30:27.869 --> 30:31.525
- I don't think it works
without this.

30:31.568 --> 30:35.746
- So Strego returns
to the ship with the flower

30:35.790 --> 30:37.531
to give to Tomm.

30:37.574 --> 30:39.402
Bella gets there first.
- Mm-hmm.

30:39.446 --> 30:40.751
- And Tomm returns.

30:40.795 --> 30:41.970
He doesn't want anyone to know

30:42.014 --> 30:43.450
that he's been working
with the rebels,

30:43.493 --> 30:45.844
so he shoots Strego,
tries to kill Bella.

30:45.887 --> 30:48.194
- Mm-hmm.
- Where's the flower?

30:48.237 --> 30:50.326
- Somewhere on that ship.

30:50.370 --> 30:52.589
♪

30:52.633 --> 30:55.114
Why would he come up
from below?

30:55.157 --> 30:58.552
Strego, he could have
stayed hidden.

30:58.595 --> 31:02.034
Bella warned him,
and he came up.

31:02.077 --> 31:04.732
He had to know death
was waiting for him.

31:04.775 --> 31:07.517
His heart was torn.

31:07.561 --> 31:10.390
Maybe death
is what he really wanted.

31:10.433 --> 31:12.783
- No Mooner would die
without reason.

31:12.827 --> 31:15.743
He'd done a wrong.
He was trying to make it right.

31:15.786 --> 31:18.572
- Strego told Tomm,
"It's done."

31:18.615 --> 31:24.186
He said, "Where one world ends,
the next one begins."

31:24.230 --> 31:29.278
Bella said she told Strego
that she was Chill's sister.

31:29.322 --> 31:31.411
Maybe that's why he came up.

31:31.454 --> 31:33.195
- He knew.

31:33.239 --> 31:35.023
He was trying
to give Bella justice.

31:35.067 --> 31:38.635
- Yes, maybe Strego
wasn't talking to Tomm.

31:38.679 --> 31:41.160
He was talking to Bella.

31:41.203 --> 31:44.990
- Arlo, you are Sherlock.

31:45.033 --> 31:47.993
Strego was trying to tell Bella
where he'd hid the flower.

31:48.036 --> 31:49.733
- Could be.
I'll go to CAT.

31:49.777 --> 31:51.170
- I'll go with you.
- Mm, no.

31:51.213 --> 31:52.736
You have other duties.

31:52.780 --> 31:56.305
- It's dangerous.

31:56.349 --> 31:59.961
- Yes, it's dangerous.

32:00.005 --> 32:02.572
The game is afoot.

32:05.184 --> 32:08.056
[soft music]

32:08.100 --> 32:12.800
♪

32:12.843 --> 32:16.108
all: Clo Wing, we honor you.

32:18.197 --> 32:21.374
Ama Tone, we honor you.

32:23.724 --> 32:27.423
Wish Spur, we honor you.

32:27.467 --> 32:34.300
♪

33:59.689 --> 34:02.692
[tense music]

34:02.736 --> 34:05.391
♪

34:05.434 --> 34:07.915
- Welcomin.

34:11.484 --> 34:14.574
- You're skipping the
celebrations, Council chair?

34:14.617 --> 34:18.969
- I have bigger-better matters
to attend.

34:19.013 --> 34:21.276
- When I came before,

34:21.320 --> 34:24.105
you opened that door
on purpose.

34:24.149 --> 34:26.673
You wanted me
to see the flower.

34:26.716 --> 34:29.719
- I gave you good-glimpse
of all this.

34:31.547 --> 34:33.854
It was the flower
that drew you back?

34:33.897 --> 34:35.595
- You told me
you didn't know Chill Spen.

34:35.638 --> 34:37.031
- I didn't.

34:37.075 --> 34:38.859
- She died
with that flower in her hand,

34:38.902 --> 34:43.211
One of a kind, Moon-made.

34:43.255 --> 34:45.648
You're working
with the rebels, Maite.

34:45.692 --> 34:49.130
- Chill didn't paint
that picture.

34:49.174 --> 34:51.915
Muffle your thinks.

34:51.959 --> 34:54.309
Open your heart.

34:54.353 --> 34:57.356
[soft music]

34:57.399 --> 35:03.144
♪

35:03.188 --> 35:05.712
What do you see?

35:07.844 --> 35:11.718
Chill's life flows through
everything in this room,

35:11.761 --> 35:14.460
but so does yours, Bella.

35:16.897 --> 35:19.682
If you do not see me
by your side,

35:19.726 --> 35:21.945
I am with you.

35:21.989 --> 35:25.993
If you do not hear my voice--
- I am with you.

35:26.036 --> 35:28.517
My absence, Love--

35:28.561 --> 35:30.432
- Is proof of nothing.

35:30.476 --> 35:34.349
♪

35:34.393 --> 35:38.658
- The letter, it was to you.

35:40.225 --> 35:44.185
- Your mother painted
that flower.

35:44.229 --> 35:46.840
All of this was Loa's.

35:50.583 --> 35:56.241
She was Earther, Mooner,

35:56.284 --> 35:59.896
Seeker, Maker, Dreamer, Lover.

35:59.940 --> 36:04.162
She was mine.

36:04.205 --> 36:10.168
♪

36:10.211 --> 36:16.043
all: ♪ Ahh

36:18.088 --> 36:21.657
- The story of Lune
is the story of us.

36:21.701 --> 36:27.097
As you return to the Mother,
we remember how we came.

36:27.141 --> 36:29.970
Back before,
when the Moon simply watched,

36:30.013 --> 36:32.625
she was lonely.

36:32.668 --> 36:36.977
She saw the Mother suffer,
but could do nothing but stare.

36:37.020 --> 36:40.067
She loved the Mother too much
to turn away,

36:40.110 --> 36:42.069
but people came from Earth.

36:42.112 --> 36:45.072
They brought IO too.

36:45.115 --> 36:49.816
And IO said to Lune,
"You are not alone anymore.

36:49.859 --> 36:53.123
"Trust that when you look away,

36:53.167 --> 36:56.562
the Mother will still be there
when you look back."

36:56.605 --> 37:00.870
Lune did not believe,
so IO gave Lune a push.

37:00.914 --> 37:03.264
♪

37:03.308 --> 37:08.530
And Lune was happy.
And there was night and day.

37:08.574 --> 37:12.099
More people came
from the Mother,

37:12.142 --> 37:15.189
and the time of Metal began.

37:15.233 --> 37:17.452
But the people
wanted wood and water.

37:17.496 --> 37:20.194
Soil and sky.

37:20.238 --> 37:24.067
Whatever question they asked,
IO answered,

37:24.111 --> 37:28.202
and the lands we call Primo
sprouted from the gray,

37:28.246 --> 37:32.162
dead rock,
and the first settlement grew.

37:32.206 --> 37:35.775
And for a time,
there was peace,

37:35.818 --> 37:38.473
but dark times came,

37:38.517 --> 37:43.304
the time of blood and tribes.

37:43.348 --> 37:46.612
IO was in danger.
The Mother sent soldiers.

37:46.655 --> 37:50.920
The tribes were put down,
and there was darkness.

37:52.052 --> 37:55.534
And IO saw what had to happen,

37:55.577 --> 37:58.493
and they began again,

37:58.537 --> 38:01.583
and the Moon said
to the Mother,

38:01.627 --> 38:05.239
"Leave me until we know
what we can be."

38:05.283 --> 38:12.115
♪

38:12.159 --> 38:15.118
[tense music]

38:15.162 --> 38:22.082
♪

38:26.565 --> 38:30.438
- "Where one world ends,
the next one begins"?

38:30.482 --> 38:33.789
♪

38:33.833 --> 38:37.315
- I've been looping here
for five years.

38:37.358 --> 38:40.579
Why did you wait?

38:40.622 --> 38:42.276
- You were hidden from me

38:42.320 --> 38:45.584
until Chill died
and IO tagged you as blood.

38:45.627 --> 38:48.978
- And my mother's things
in the box from Chill?

38:49.022 --> 38:52.504
How would Loa have known
Chill was her daughter?

38:52.547 --> 38:55.028
That's kept hidden.
- I have no answer.

38:55.071 --> 38:58.901
Loa would wander off

38:58.945 --> 39:02.122
through the Glade, into Primo.

39:02.165 --> 39:04.298
I suspected
she went over the wall

39:04.342 --> 39:06.953
into the Fringelands too.

39:06.996 --> 39:12.698
One day, she wandered back,
and she knew.

39:13.786 --> 39:16.005
She was never at peace
until the dark path

39:16.049 --> 39:18.530
was before her.

39:18.573 --> 39:21.402
She lived to be the light.

39:21.446 --> 39:23.578
- What was she looking for?

39:23.622 --> 39:27.147
- What winds
the Seeker's heart?

39:27.190 --> 39:31.673
The Grail, the empty road?
Does it matter?

39:31.717 --> 39:34.502
They go where the rest
of us fear to go.

39:34.546 --> 39:37.375
- The rest of us
are still alive.

39:37.418 --> 39:39.986
♪

39:40.029 --> 39:43.424
- Doda.

39:43.468 --> 39:46.253
- What are you doing here?

39:46.296 --> 39:49.648
- Just checking up on you.

39:49.691 --> 39:53.434
- Gratz.
I needed some breath.

39:53.478 --> 39:56.524
[soft music]

39:56.568 --> 39:58.874
- I'm scared.

39:58.918 --> 40:05.881
♪

40:06.882 --> 40:10.495
- I know.

40:10.538 --> 40:14.455
If you choose the right way,
the hard way,

40:14.499 --> 40:17.589
Truelune will never
let you down.

40:17.632 --> 40:21.027
And Wish, wherever you go,

40:21.070 --> 40:23.551
I'll always be with you.

40:23.595 --> 40:26.554
♪

40:26.598 --> 40:29.252
My son.

40:29.296 --> 40:36.129
♪

40:52.928 --> 40:54.800
- Hmm.

40:59.631 --> 41:02.111
- Whatever part you think
I'm playing in this, Maite,

41:02.155 --> 41:03.504
you're wrong.

41:03.548 --> 41:05.550
I stumbled into this mess.

41:05.593 --> 41:07.116
I wanted nothing
to do with any of it,

41:07.160 --> 41:12.208
but I see now
the Bridge must happen.

41:12.252 --> 41:15.473
It can't be allowed to fail.
The First Wave needs to leave.

41:15.516 --> 41:17.736
- We will cross the Bridge,
but not this way.

41:17.779 --> 41:20.042
- There is no other way.
- There is.

41:20.086 --> 41:21.914
Others have arrived.

41:23.611 --> 41:26.396
- Others?

41:26.440 --> 41:28.442
- Drawn across the void.

41:28.486 --> 41:31.532
Our human flicker
was too dim to see,

41:31.576 --> 41:35.144
but IO's flame shines bright.

41:35.188 --> 41:36.668
- Aliens?

41:38.887 --> 41:43.936
Here for IO?
And you've made contact?

41:43.979 --> 41:47.940
- Your mother was the first.
She told me of a passage.

41:47.983 --> 41:50.986
I did not believe,
but the signs come now,

41:51.030 --> 41:54.033
fast and furious.

41:54.076 --> 41:57.819
Even as you doubt me,
you are the proof.

41:57.863 --> 42:01.519
They speak to IO,
and IO has brought you here.

42:01.562 --> 42:04.043
- Why me?

42:04.086 --> 42:06.088
- Your mother didn't die.

42:06.132 --> 42:09.222
She wandered off
and did not return.

42:09.265 --> 42:11.267
IO marked her dead,

42:11.311 --> 42:13.792
but I am heart-sure
she's with them.

42:13.835 --> 42:18.318
I feel it, as do you.

42:18.361 --> 42:21.495
The seeker has found the Grail.

42:21.539 --> 42:24.454
It's time for us to find her.

42:24.498 --> 42:27.370
[explosions and screams]

42:27.414 --> 42:30.373
[dramatic music]

42:30.417 --> 42:35.335
♪

42:35.378 --> 42:37.555
- Maite?

42:37.598 --> 42:44.562
♪

42:52.482 --> 42:56.008
- "Where one world ends,

42:56.051 --> 42:59.533
the next one begins."

42:59.577 --> 43:02.536
[tense music]

43:02.580 --> 43:07.672
♪

43:07.715 --> 43:10.718
[grunts]

43:10.762 --> 43:13.547
♪

43:13.591 --> 43:16.202
Ah.

43:16.245 --> 43:23.122
♪

43:26.865 --> 43:29.215
Hello, flower.

43:29.258 --> 43:31.783
♪

43:31.826 --> 43:34.916
- Th-thanks.

43:34.960 --> 43:39.225
[dramatic music]

43:39.268 --> 43:41.662
Maite was spotted
going into Primo.

43:41.706 --> 43:44.186
Into the wilderness?

43:44.230 --> 43:45.710
She thinks The Bridge
is doomed.

43:45.753 --> 43:48.713
We figured out
that it's a compass rose

43:48.756 --> 43:50.279
like the ancient sailors
used.

43:50.323 --> 43:52.717
We need to see
where it leads.

43:54.022 --> 43:55.415
The ships are landing.

43:55.458 --> 43:57.417
Everything's
going to be okay.

43:57.460 --> 44:00.376
Drop the flower,
and I'll kill you.

44:00.420 --> 44:01.639
What is this?

44:01.682 --> 44:03.031
It's not for us.

44:03.075 --> 44:05.817
What have we unlocked?

44:09.168 --> 44:16.088
♪
